            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Ruth.2:1-4:22",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3ERuth%202%3A1-4%3A22%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_1%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ERuth%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ERuth%20Works%20in%20Boaz%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Field%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20there%20was%20a%20wealthy%20and%20influential%20man%20in%20Bethlehem%20named%20Boaz%2C%20who%20was%20a%20relative%20of%20Naomi%26%23x2019%3Bs%20husband%2C%20Elimelech.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_2%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20Ruth%20the%20Moabite%20said%20to%20Naomi%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%20me%20go%20out%20into%20the%20harvest%20fields%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20stalks%20of%20grain%20left%20behind%20by%20anyone%20who%20is%20kind%20enough%20to%20let%20me%20do%20it.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ENaomi%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAll%20right%2C%20my%20daughter%2C%20go%20ahead.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_3%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Ruth%20went%20out%20to%20gather%20grain%20behind%20the%20harvesters.%20And%20as%20it%20happened%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20working%20in%20a%20field%20that%20belonged%20to%20Boaz%2C%20the%20relative%20of%20her%20father-in-law%2C%20Elimelech.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_4%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EWhile%20she%20was%20there%2C%20Boaz%20arrived%20from%20Bethlehem%20and%20greeted%20the%20harvesters.%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20be%20with%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20bless%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20harvesters%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_5%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Boaz%20asked%20his%20foreman%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWho%20is%20that%20young%20woman%20over%20there%3F%20Who%20does%20she%20belong%20to%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_6%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20foreman%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShe%20is%20the%20young%20woman%20from%20Moab%20who%20came%20back%20with%20Naomi.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_7%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EShe%20asked%20me%20this%20morning%20if%20she%20could%20gather%20grain%20behind%20the%20harvesters.%20She%20has%20been%20hard%20at%20work%20ever%20since%2C%20except%20for%20a%20few%20minutes%26%23x2019%3B%20rest%20in%20the%20shelter.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_8%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBoaz%20went%20over%20and%20said%20to%20Ruth%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%2C%20my%20daughter.%20Stay%20right%20here%20with%20us%20when%20you%20gather%20grain%3B%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20go%20to%20any%20other%20fields.%20Stay%20right%20behind%20the%20young%20women%20working%20in%20my%20field.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_9%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESee%20which%20part%20of%20the%20field%20they%20are%20harvesting%2C%20and%20then%20follow%20them.%20I%20have%20warned%20the%20young%20men%20not%20to%20treat%20you%20roughly.%20And%20when%20you%20are%20thirsty%2C%20help%20yourself%20to%20the%20water%20they%20have%20drawn%20from%20the%20well.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_10%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ERuth%20fell%20at%20his%20feet%20and%20thanked%20him%20warmly.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20have%20I%20done%20to%20deserve%20such%20kindness%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20she%20asked.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20only%20a%20foreigner.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_11%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20I%20know%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Boaz%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BBut%20I%20also%20know%20about%20everything%20you%20have%20done%20for%20your%20mother-in-law%20since%20the%20death%20of%20your%20husband.%20I%20have%20heard%20how%20you%20left%20your%20father%20and%20mother%20and%20your%20own%20land%20to%20live%20here%20among%20complete%20strangers.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_12%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20under%20whose%20wings%20you%20have%20come%20to%20take%20refuge%2C%20reward%20you%20fully%20for%20what%20you%20have%20done.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_13%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20hope%20I%20continue%20to%20please%20you%2C%20sir%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20she%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20have%20comforted%20me%20by%20speaking%20so%20kindly%20to%20me%2C%20even%20though%20I%20am%20not%20one%20of%20your%20workers.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_14%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20mealtime%20Boaz%20called%20to%20her%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BCome%20over%20here%2C%20and%20help%20yourself%20to%20some%20food.%20You%20can%20dip%20your%20bread%20in%20the%20sour%20wine.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20she%20sat%20with%20his%20harvesters%2C%20and%20Boaz%20gave%20her%20some%20roasted%20grain%20to%20eat.%20She%20ate%20all%20she%20wanted%20and%20still%20had%20some%20left%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_15%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Ruth%20went%20back%20to%20work%20again%2C%20Boaz%20ordered%20his%20young%20men%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%20her%20gather%20grain%20right%20among%20the%20sheaves%20without%20stopping%20her.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_16%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20pull%20out%20some%20heads%20of%20barley%20from%20the%20bundles%20and%20drop%20them%20on%20purpose%20for%20her.%20Let%20her%20pick%20them%20up%2C%20and%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20give%20her%20a%20hard%20time!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_17%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Ruth%20gathered%20barley%20there%20all%20day%2C%20and%20when%20she%20beat%20out%20the%20grain%20that%20evening%2C%20it%20filled%20an%20entire%20basket.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E2%3A17%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eit%20was%20about%20an%20ephah%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B20%26%23xA0%3Bquarts%20or%2022%26%23xA0%3Bliters%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_18%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EShe%20carried%20it%20back%20into%20town%20and%20showed%20it%20to%20her%20mother-in-law.%20Ruth%20also%20gave%20her%20the%20roasted%20grain%20that%20was%20left%20over%20from%20her%20meal.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_19%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhere%20did%20you%20gather%20all%20this%20grain%20today%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Naomi%20asked.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhere%20did%20you%20work%3F%20May%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20bless%20the%20one%20who%20helped%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ESo%20Ruth%20told%20her%20mother-in-law%20about%20the%20man%20in%20whose%20field%20she%20had%20worked.%20She%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20man%20I%20worked%20with%20today%20is%20named%20Boaz.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_20%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20bless%20him!%26%23x201D%3B%20Naomi%20told%20her%20daughter-in-law.%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20is%20showing%20his%20kindness%20to%20us%20as%20well%20as%20to%20your%20dead%20husband.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E2%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eto%20the%20living%20and%20to%20the%20dead.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20That%20man%20is%20one%20of%20our%20closest%20relatives%2C%20one%20of%20our%20family%20redeemers.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_21%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Ruth%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E2%3A21%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ERuth%20the%20Moabite.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20more%2C%20Boaz%20even%20told%20me%20to%20come%20back%20and%20stay%20with%20his%20harvesters%20until%20the%20entire%20harvest%20is%20completed.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_22%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BGood!%26%23x201D%3B%20Naomi%20exclaimed.%20%26%23x201C%3BDo%20as%20he%20said%2C%20my%20daughter.%20Stay%20with%20his%20young%20women%20right%20through%20the%20whole%20harvest.%20You%20might%20be%20harassed%20in%20other%20fields%2C%20but%20you%26%23x2019%3Bll%20be%20safe%20with%20him.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_2_23%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%222%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Ruth%20worked%20alongside%20the%20women%20in%20Boaz%26%23x2019%3Bs%20fields%20and%20gathered%20grain%20with%20them%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20barley%20harvest.%20Then%20she%20continued%20working%20with%20them%20through%20the%20wheat%20harvest%20in%20early%20summer.%20And%20all%20the%20while%20she%20lived%20with%20her%20mother-in-law.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ruth_3_1%22%20bk%3D%22ruth%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ERuth%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3